{
  "stem": "16571.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 24.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And the girls felt so sorry for us who were dishing out this food that they never even tore our cards up, and we used to eat it, then line up, and have another lot, and so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And gradually, you sort of got on your feet, and-- and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And-- and so it went.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "So it went.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "That was in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "But it was very, very-- it was-- well, the worst camp I've ever been to.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And I've been to three.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "I didn't know what was happening in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "I wasn't long enough there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "In Buchenwald, as I said, I was lucky.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "Whereas in Belsen, it was the end of sort of the last four or five months of the war, and they-- it was just terrible.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "We used to wait certain times for the-- the dentist and the doctors, but not for hours for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "They were throwing out peelings of potatoes from the windows above, and we were-- about 20 of us were diving in the mud-- that's how hungry we were-- to pick up-- pick these peelings from potatoes or carrots or whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "And that is hunger, when people have to dive in mud and things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "And we were lucky to-- that we sort of-- the rest of the people didn't find out, because they would kill you.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "But the worst thing which ever-- I'm jumping.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "You see, I don't remember-- the worst thing which ever happened to me in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "One morning, I heard a commotion.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "And I went to the door.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "And apparently somebody opened one of these barrels of soup, what some people got-- because some people did work for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 89,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] How do--",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
